WEBVTT

00:00.238 --> 00:01.672
<i>Previously on The Borgias...</i>

00:01.923 --> 00:03.991
<i>The Jews from Constantinople.</i>

00:03.992 --> 00:05.358
<i>More of them come every day.</i>

00:05.426 --> 00:07.293
You were driven
out by the Turks.

00:07.361 --> 00:08.628
We offer you a home,

00:08.695 --> 00:09.894
<i>a place to prosper.</i>

00:09.962 --> 00:11.629
And in return?

00:11.697 --> 00:13.430
<i>So the King</i>
<i>of Naples died.</i>

00:13.498 --> 00:14.964
<i>Most horribly.</i>

00:15.032 --> 00:16.165
<i>There are several</i>
<i>claimants, I've heard.</i>

00:16.233 --> 00:17.498
<i>Is your Alfonso</i>
<i>among them?</i>

00:17.566 --> 00:19.465
There are two in
line in front of him.

00:19.533 --> 00:20.799
Your Highness.

00:20.866 --> 00:22.900
The last French invasion
ended in disaster.

00:22.968 --> 00:25.769
Maybe if the next was under
Italian leadership...

00:25.836 --> 00:28.271
King Louis
of France invades our shores

00:28.339 --> 00:29.739
without our permission!

00:29.807 --> 00:31.073
He has our permission.

00:31.141 --> 00:32.876
You would bring an
army into our land.

00:32.943 --> 00:35.178
I would eliminate
the Sforza dynasty.

00:35.246 --> 00:36.813
Ludovico first.

00:36.881 --> 00:38.081
<i>What is this?</i>

00:38.149 --> 00:40.084
A message from Lady
Catherina Sforza

00:40.151 --> 00:41.552
treating for peace.

00:41.619 --> 00:43.320
This is a bluff.
Burn it.

00:43.388 --> 00:45.189
Catherina Sforza
has no more interest

00:45.257 --> 00:46.757
<i>in suing for peace</i>
<i>than I do.</i>

00:46.825 --> 00:49.394
Are you sick?
What's the matter?

00:49.495 --> 00:51.029
Plague!

00:51.097 --> 00:53.265
<i>This king</i>
<i>desires more than Naples.</i>

00:53.332 --> 00:55.667
He has an equal
fondness for Milan.

00:58.404 --> 00:59.504
<i>My Lord Sforza?</i>

00:59.572 --> 01:01.005
<i>My mother was right.</i>

01:01.072 --> 01:02.373
<i>Come tomorrow's dawn there</i>
<i>will be rivers of blood.</i>

01:02.440 --> 01:04.040
The gates are open, my lord.

01:04.141 --> 01:05.542
The city looks unguarded.

01:05.609 --> 01:06.676
Welcome to Milan.

01:06.744 --> 01:08.478
Where's Ludovico Sforza?
Gone.

01:08.545 --> 01:09.906
<i>We have Milan, my lord.</i>

01:09.946 --> 01:11.480
No, the French have Milan.

01:11.548 --> 01:13.848
<i>And Ludovico Sforza lives</i>
<i>to fight another day.</i>

01:13.916 --> 01:15.116
DAMN HIM!

